            <thetext>Widget._visualPropertyCheck may throw an error message saying &quot;Element must be created previously!&quot;
When a large part of JavaScript gets executed at once, it is very difficult to tell which widget caused this error.
At least in my case the stack trace only shows qooxdoo function calls - and I&#39;m lost.

Would it be possible the include further information? The classname would be helpful, and maybe the element type if available.
Or is there any other way to make this error less painful?</thetext>
